   <head>Transforming the XML using Oxygen</head>
   <p>Instructions of how to use the epidoc XSLT stylesheets with your own epidoc files. This was
      written using Oxygen v7.1</p>
   <list>
      <item>With the XML file open in Oxygen, click the "Apply transformation scenario" button.</item>
      <item>In the "Configure transformation scenario" window, click on "new" to create a new
         scenario.</item>
      <item>In the XSLT tab, enter the path for force-namespace-tei.xsl into XSL URL</item>
      <item>Click on "Parameters", "Add". Enter in "Name", 'standalonecss'. In "Value", enter the
         path for the location of epidocscreen.css.</item>
      <item>Back in the XSLT tab, click on "Additional XSLT stylesheets", "Add". Enter the path for
         epidoc.xsl</item>
      <item>Return to the XSLT tab, in the Output tab, select "Prompt for file" and "Open in
         browser".</item>
      <item>Returning to the original "Configure transformation scenario" window, click "Transform
         now".</item>
      <item>Save to a desired location and see the results!</item>
   </list>
